ensitive measurements will lead to very\naccurate mass loss estimation in these supernovae. One also expects to detect\ngravitationally lensed supernovae in far away Universe in the SKA bands. Radio\ncounterparts of the gravitational waves are likely to become a reality once SKA\ncomes online. In addition, SKA is likely to discover various new kinds of\ntransients.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Wed, 26 Oct 2016 05:48:46 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Mon, 31 Oct 2016 19:26:34 GMT"}],"update_date":"2016-11-23"}
